In geometry, the '5-cell' is a four-dimensional object bounded by 5 tetrahedral
cells. It is also known as the 'pentachoron', 'pentatope', or 'tetrahedral
hyperpyramid'. It is a 4-simplex, the simplest possible convex regular 4-
polytope (four-dimensional analogue of a polyhedron), and is analogous to the
tetrahedron in three dimensions and the triangle in two dimensions.

The 'regular 5-cell' is bounded by regular tetrahedra, and is one of the six
regular convex polychora, represented by SchlÃ¤fli symbol {3,3,3}.
